.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"directly, and do not create your own subclasses of this class. The shape","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"classes correspond to the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Geometry","type":"text"},{"text":" object","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"types in the GeoJSON standard, but some have nonstandard names for backwards","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"compatibility.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Although you do not create instances of this class directly, you can use its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape\/shapeWithData:encoding:error:","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" factory method to create one of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"concrete subclasses of "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" noted above from GeoJSON data. To access a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"shape’s attributes, use the corresponding "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNFeature","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" class instead."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can add shapes to the map by adding them to an "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource"},{"type":"text","text":" object."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Configure the appearance of an "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource"},{"type":"text","text":"’s or "},{"isActive":true,"typ